<p> 
A pseudo-random number generator is a computer program that generates numbers that appear to be 
random (that is, without any discernable pattern).  In fact, however, the program is completely
predictable and, with the same parameters, will produce the same numeric output.
</p>
<p>
The parameter to such a generator&mdash;there is generally only one&mdash;is called 
a <a href="glossary.php?term=seed">seed</a>.</p>